Imperial Tobacco, HSBC, Rio Tinto: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-21T06:48:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/arena-leisure-dtz-hsbc-rio-tinto-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  Futures on the benchmark FTSE 100 Index added 0.1 percent
to 5,345 at 7:47 a.m. in  London . The FTSE 100 rose 104.15
points, or 2 percent, to 5,363.71 yesterday. The FTSE All-Share
Index climbed 1.8 percent to 2,777.05, while Ireland’s ISEQ
Index advanced 1.5 percent to 2,492.91.  Arena Leisure Plc (ARE)  : The U.K. race-track owner said
it received a proposal from the Reuben Brothers in relation to a
possible offer for the company. The stock jumped 17 percent to
36.25 pence.  DTZ Holdings Plc (DTZ)  : The U.K. property broker said it
isn’t aware of the reason for the decline in its share price.
The stock plunged 15 percent to 26.5 pence.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : National Bank of Canada, the
country’s sixth-largest lender, agreed to buy the Canadian
investment advisory business of HSBC for C$206 million ($207
million) in cash. The shares advanced 1.9 percent to 520.9
pence.  Imperial Tobacco Group Plc (IMT)  : The maker of West and
Davidoff cigarettes forecast higher full-year sales, led by
growth in eastern Europe and Asia. Net revenue from tobacco will
probably increase 2 percent excluding currency shifts, the
company said. The shares rose 2.7 percent to 2,093 pence.  Rio Tinto Group (RIO LN): The world’s second-largest mining
company by sales is in talks to ensure power supplies for its
Oyu Tolgoi copper project in Mongolia. The stock increased 0.9
percent to 3,537.5 pence.  Tesco Plc (TSCO)  : The U.K.’s largest retailer said
British customers cannot order groceries and some non-food goods
online because of a “rare technical glitch.” The stock gained
0.9 percent to 371.15 pence.  Thomas Cook Group Plc (TCG)  : The company named Frank
Meysman chairman-designate with effect from Oct. 1. Meysman will
become chairman when Michael Beckett retires from the board, it
said. The shares rose 2.1 percent to 41.35 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
